Course consists individual work in Moodle course (with the help of texts, videos, photos) and individually reading performing arts theoretical texts and plays. In seminars and practices students are analysing the important trends and specific moments of performing arts and cultural history, examples of performances and plays, solve the thematical exercises as a group work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the development of the main performing arts` research methods in regard to the movement from dramatic to postdramatic theatre. In addition, the practical skills to analyse performing arts is developed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course student:
-knows the basic conceptions and viewpoints of performing arts; research methods (such as theatre
semiotics, fenomenology and theatre sociology);
-is able to choose the appropriate method and to use elementary research skills for analysing the
performances;
-is able to analyse the influence of different contexts (aesthetical, cultural, social etc) in a process of
developing the meaning and perception of the performance.
